There is no natural place to draw a line between these two, however.
A biological body augmented with nanotech may use materials we don't
normally associate with biology.  There is a continuum between ordinary
biological bodies and things like cyborgs and robots.

As far as uploading, this does suggest an architecture where the seat
of consciousness is within stationary structures while manipulation is
done via remotes.  However there is nothing inherent in the upload concept
which would prevent some or all of the consciousness moving into the
