> synapses, axons, dendrites: is it chemically and topologically driven?

Likely a bit of both. We don't know yet, but there are definitely
chemical signals and perhaps others.

> A function like: grow toward that chemical source at a rate
> proportional to its importance?

Sounds like a good first approximation. There has been some
theoretical work on how the chemical gradients ought to look to give
an optimal growth performance, and they seem to fit reality quite
well.

