        21st Century Medicine (21CM) is the only company in the
world with a well-funded research program to achieve suspended
animation.  21CM occupies two buildings in Rancho Cucamonga,
California that are about a quarter of a mile apart.  The first building
houses the company's Critical Care Medicine Division, which is
conducting advanced research to restore clinically dead patients
to life (resuscitation), and to induce rapid, reversible, full-body
cooling in patients suffering from hyperthermia (dangerously high
body temperature).

